<section id="workflow" class="sf-marketing-section">
    <div class="sf-public-container">
        <div class="sf-section-heading">
            <p class="sf-marketing-eyebrow">How it works</p>
            <h2>Provision once, operate where the work happens.</h2>
            <p>The rollout path stays simple: provision the tenant once, then let the business operate inside the surface that matches the daily workflow.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sf-workflow-grid">
            <article class="sf-workflow-step">
                <span>01</span>
                <h3>Subscribe and provision</h3>
                <p>Platform administrators control the plan catalog and provision businesses into the tenant directory.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="sf-workflow-step">
                <span>02</span>
                <h3>Use SMS on web</h3>
                <p>The tenant enters `/{tenant}/sms/` for service intake, assignments, customer handling, and invoicing.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="sf-workflow-step">
                <span>03</span>
                <h3>Use MLS on desktop</h3>
                <p>Premium businesses extend into `/{tenant}/mls/` for micro-lending records, schedules, and collections work.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="sf-workflow-step">
                <span>04</span>
                <h3>Stay tenant-scoped</h3>
                <p>Every business remains isolated to its own domain while the platform keeps clean root-domain oversight.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
